Text:
In the expansive library, Beta searches through the
books with the rest of the squad.

If this skill was commonplace during that era, then
there's no denying the exceptional nature of the
Cult's technical prowess.

Their power lies with the demon... I get that, but
where can we find the knowledge needed to acquire
that power?
Beta hears an approaching sound and lifts her gaze.
Ow?!
...Oof.
I told you not to go touching everything...
How was I supposed to know there'd be a slide?!
Anyway, we've managed to get inside the tower...

Who would've thought that place would lead there and
then connect to here...
By the way, where exactly are we?
We should be right under the Crimson Tower, but...
You're in the Crimson Tower's underground library.
Good grief...
We should get rid of any witnesses...
But I guess that isn't an option.
...It looks like we've been found out already.
That's why I told you to be careful...

Look, I'm sorry. But we'd have been discovered one
way or the other.
I have no intention of fighting you, Ms. Claire.
...You know me?

You're Claire Kagenou, the winner of the Bushin
Festival.
I guess my name's gotten around.

She doesn't seem to be a vampire, so we shouldn't
waste time on pointless battles.
...Besides, she's got backup.
Hey, why's Lady Beta keeping her face hidden?
Quiet!

Fair enough. Tell me who you are and what you want.
Once I'm sure you aren't my enemy, we'd be happy to
back down.

Who I am and what I want, huh? Well, you're right.
Just like you, I'm here to invade the Crimson Tower.
I need more details.
I'm afraid that would take a while.
Give me the specifics, but make it concise.
My, how particular.

My name is Beta, and I work for the Shadow Garden.
I came to the Crimson Tower because I have some
business to attend to.

Shadow Garden? Aren't you the ones who burned down
the Academy? What, are you planning to burn down this
tower as well?
What?!

Hmm... How much to tell you? There are things I'm
allowed to say and things I'm not, after all.

How about this? We're conducting research on
possession for certain reasons, and we wanted
a blood sample from a Progenitor.
On possession...?!

What do the possessed have to do with the Progenitor
Vampires?

There's a possibility that the blood of the possessed
and the blood of the Progenitors share the same
origin and that the two merely diverged as they were
inherited from parent to child.

Over the course of our research, we arrived at a
certain hypothesis. To confirm it, we'll need to
examine the Blood Queen, who is the original
vampire Progenitor.
The possessed and the vampires?
You dare blaspheme the Progenitors?

It's only a theory, and we certainly mean no insult
to the Progenitors. We just wanted a sample so we
could check for ourselves.

Why does the thought make you so mad, Ms. Ancient
Vampire Hunter? I mean, you've been hunting them
for the better part of a thousand years.
You know who I am...
I've heard rumors.
You stay out of our way, and we'll stay out of yours.
Can we agree on that?

There's one thing I want to know. Is there a way to
cure the possessed?

I'm...afraid I can't tell you. However, I will say
you personally don't have anything to worry about.
What do you mean by that?
Exactly what I said.

...Fine. Let's go, Mary. If we stick around here,
we won't make it in time to save my brother!
*gasp*
Your brother?

He was abducted by the people here. We need to hurry,
or he'll end up as a sacrifice to the Blood Queen.
I see...
Is it true?!
Is it true that Ci
But I... I'm sorry...

Are we done here? Just remember not to get in our
way.
One last thing.

Is there really no way you can try to re-create the
"Haven"?
*gasp*
Mary?
Hey, wait
*sigh*
I'm disappointed in you, Number 666.
My deepest apologies.

Lambda spoke highly of your skills, and Alpha has
great expectations for you. But this is a mark
against you. Also, you two should have stopped her.
My apologies...
Sorry.

Our mission is strictly to recover a sample of
Progenitor blood for the lab. Master Shadow
will handle the Blood Queen.

We needn't worry about the sacrifice or anything
else.
Understood, No. 666?
Yes, ma'am.
Keeping her safe is part of the job, Beta.
